value.name: Cape Barren Island - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Cape Barren Island, officially truwana / Cape Barren Island, is a 478-square-kilometre (185 sq mi) island in the Bass Strait, off the north east coast of Tasmania, Australia. It is the second largest island of the Furneaux Group; Flinders Island lies to the north, with the smaller Clarke Island to the south.

value.name: Cape Barren Island - Flinders Council
value.snippet: Cape Barren Island has an area of 478.4 km 2 (184.7 sq mi). In 2006, t he population of the whole of Cape Barren Island was 268, with most people living in the settlement of Cape Barren Island, also called The Corner, on the North West Coast.

value.name: Cape Barren Island - About Australia
value.snippet: Cape Barren Island is a small Tasmanian Rural Location within the local government area of Flinders, it is located approximately 285kms from the capital Hobart covering an area of 580.405 square kilometres. Cape Barren Island has a recorded population of 66 residents and is within the Australian Eastern Daylight Time zone Australia/Hobart.
